Anatomy is torture to me, because you can never truly get to the bottom of things. Like if you have a ligament, discovered by a doctor named Dr. John, it's probably called "John's ligament". And you just have to crudely memorize it by brute forcing the name into your brain.

You have to make non-sensical associations scraped off culture like "John-Ligament, John-Ligma, Ligma-Johnson" to remember it, but that's artifice. Anatomy textbook should offer information on name etymology, why parents picked it, how he got interested in specific ligament, etc.

I hate using technology, even if it consists of me crafting fake associations in my mind. I should know who he was named after, his family history, life. This is why when Leibniz was hired to write the Brunswick family's history, he started writing about paleontology and fossils.
